This paper focuses on deep convolutional neural networks for face identification, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also explores the contribution of different preprocessing approaches to the network's performance, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses transfer learning and SoftMax classifier, which are common techniques in multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
